        </div>
        <h3 class="tc-atlas-h">Devtools detection</h3>
        <p class="tc-atlas-d">Console-open heuristics, focus loss, paste-event volume, and clipboard read attempts all stream to the session ledger. Each is a soft signal, never a hard fail.</p>
        <a class="tc-atlas-link" href="/aquintutor/exams">Read &nbsp;&rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="tc-atlas-card">
        <div class="tc-atlas-icon">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2 4 6v6c0 5 4 9 8 10 4-1 8-5 8-10V6l-8-4z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="tc-atlas-h">Integrity score</h3>
        <p class="tc-atlas-d">A composite 0-100 number combining face stability, focus loss, paste volume, and ambient audio. Below 75 routes the session to a human reviewer; above 95 is auto-released.</p>
        <a class="tc-atlas-link" href="/aquintutor/exams">Read &nbsp;&rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ADAPTIVE ENGINE -->
  <section class="tc-section">
    <div class="tc-sec-top">
      <div>
        <div class="tc-sec-eye">Adaptive engine &middot; IRT routing</div>
        <h2 class="tc-sec-title">The next question is <em>tuned to you</em>.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tc-adapt-wrap">
      <div class="tc-adapt-text">
        <p>
          On adaptive tests, the engine maintains a running estimate of candidate ability <strong>theta</strong> after every response. It picks the next item whose difficulty <strong>b</strong> is closest to current theta — this is the most informative item under the 2-parameter logistic model.
        </p>
        <p>
          As the response stream lengthens, theta tightens. Once the standard error of measurement drops below the test threshold (typically 0.30 in logit units), the session terminates and the score is locked.
        </p>
        <p>
          Click <strong>Step</strong> to walk through one routing decision. Click <strong>Reset</strong> to start over. The orange branch is the path the engine actually took.
        </p>
        <div class="tc-adapt-formula">
          P(correct | theta, b, a) = 1 / (1 + e<sup>-1.7 a (theta - b)</sup>)<br/>
          info(item) = a<sup>2</sup> &middot; P &middot; (1 - P) &nbsp;&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>pick max info</em>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tc-adapt-canvas-wrap">
        <canvas class="tc-adapt-canvas" id="tc-adapt-canvas"></canvas>
        <div class="tc-adapt-controls">
          <button class="tc-adapt-btn" id="tc-adapt-step">Step</button>
          <button class="tc-adapt-btn" id="tc-adapt-reset">Reset</button>
          <span style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:#7A6F68;margin-left:auto;align-self:center;" id="tc-adapt-status">Step 0 &middot; theta = 0.00 &middot; SE = 1.00</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

